    "longBusinessSummary": "Ha Do Group Joint Stock Company, together with its subsidiaries, engages in the electricity generation, transmission, and distribution activities in Vietnam. It operates through Real Estate Trading; Electricity Generation and Trading; and Construction Activities, Rental Business and Other Activities segments. The company is involved in the investment, construction, and trading in real estate; operation of hotels and resorts; office rental; export and transmission floors; real estate auction; M&A real estate projects; design and construction investment consultancy; real estate operation and management; construction and business of industrial park infrastructure; exploitation, treatment, and supply of clean water; and real estate services, that includes land transfer, and sale of construction items for real estate projects. It also engages in consulting services on the design and investment in the construction of energy projects, and distribution of real estate projects; investment, construction, installation, management, and operation of hydropower, renewable energy, wind, and solar power projects; M&A of energy and green projects; investment in products in the capital, debt, and stock market; and investing, contributing capital, and M&A of potential businesses and projects, as well as urban area, apartment, and villa projects. The company was founded in 1990 and is headquartered in Hanoi, Vietnam.",
